        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 27 at 10:49PM CDT by NWS Aberdeen SD</headline>
        <description>At 1049 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Fort Pierre, moving northeast at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Grey Goose, Overlook Rec Area, Fort Pierre, and Pierre.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
